WEBVTT

00:00.601 --> 00:02.000
 Well, you scared
 the shit out of us.
 How's the kid?

00:02.001 --> 00:03.868
             I think he's yours.

00:03.870 --> 00:05.537
I'll make sure that everything's
 ready for you both

00:05.539 --> 00:07.939
 when you come back
    to the house.

00:07.942 --> 00:09.674
        210.
                  Bullshit!

00:09.676 --> 00:12.544
[ Quietly ] Calm down.
         You short me 150 grand,

00:12.546 --> 00:14.078
             then you expect me
                to calm down?

00:14.080 --> 00:16.414
There are other more lucrative
opportunities coming --

00:16.416 --> 00:19.417
another job.
               I'm not working
         for that asshole again.

00:19.419 --> 00:21.219
      This one
   could be bigger
                        No.

00:21.221 --> 00:22.755
  My brother's kind of strange.

00:22.757 --> 00:25.490
            -Janine.
        -Yeah. [ Laughs ]

00:25.492 --> 00:26.825
     Jed's stockpiling gold.

00:26.827 --> 00:28.893
   Young Jed: Yeah, you watch.
         I will survive

00:28.895 --> 00:31.029
       when the world goes
          pear-shaped.

00:31.031 --> 00:32.030
            Will you?

00:32.031 --> 00:33.432
          [ Grunting ]

00:33.434 --> 00:35.100
     Psycho son-of-a-bitch.

00:35.102 --> 00:36.368
                I'm pregnant.

00:36.370 --> 00:38.170
         How long have you known
                that Adrian's

00:38.172 --> 00:40.104
                been talking
                to the feds?

00:40.106 --> 00:41.306
                 Handle it.

00:41.308 --> 00:43.108
    Or I'll have to turn it over
                  to Pope.

00:43.110 --> 00:45.377
              You seen Angela?
       No.

00:45.379 --> 00:47.512
         I'm looking for Angela.
             Have you seen her?

00:47.514 --> 00:49.982
 Kalani: Yesterday.
She was with Julia's kid.

00:49.984 --> 00:51.383
           She pick up from you?

00:51.385 --> 00:53.117
 You know how it is.
If Angela wants dope,

00:53.119 --> 00:54.919
she's gonna find it.

00:54.921 --> 00:56.989
                  The hell?
             Let go of me, Pope!

00:56.991 --> 01:00.124
          -Where is it?
     -There's nothing there!

01:00.126 --> 01:01.794
  No, no, no! Stop!

01:01.796 --> 01:03.061
        Pope!

01:03.063 --> 01:08.667
                     ♪♪

01:08.669 --> 01:14.606
      ♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:14.608 --> 01:18.610
      ♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:18.612 --> 01:21.680
      ♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:24.618 --> 01:30.288
         ♪ One they know
      that I cannot take ♪

01:30.290 --> 01:33.625
 ♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:33.627 --> 01:36.929
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:40.634 --> 01:43.502
 ♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:43.504 --> 01:47.372
    ♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:47.374 --> 01:51.243
     ♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:51.245 --> 01:54.979
  ♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:54.981 --> 01:59.117
      ♪ I've got a big black,
         big black hole ♪

01:59.119 --> 02:03.188
     ♪ Got a big black hole
         inside of me ♪

02:03.190 --> 02:04.857
            ♪ Got a ♪

02:08.395 --> 02:10.461
         [ Door opens ]

02:10.464 --> 02:14.999
        [ Distant music,
      indistinct chatter ]

02:15.001 --> 02:22.140
                     ♪♪

02:22.142 --> 02:23.675
         [ Bell dings ]

02:23.677 --> 02:26.211
               [ Indistinct ]

02:26.213 --> 02:32.417
                     ♪♪

02:32.419 --> 02:33.952
  [ Sighs ]
                      Morning.

02:33.954 --> 02:36.421
    Good morning.

02:36.423 --> 02:38.490
     Let me get
   some pancakes.

02:38.492 --> 02:40.959
                 Sure, hon.
           Blueberry or regular?

02:40.961 --> 02:42.494
           Blueberry.

02:42.496 --> 02:43.828
                Extra syrup.

02:43.830 --> 02:46.431
        Mmm.
Craving sugar, right?

02:46.433 --> 02:47.900
                 I guess so.

02:47.902 --> 02:48.967
     [ Laughs ]

02:48.969 --> 02:51.904
     I was, too,
  about that time.

02:51.906 --> 02:53.972
       Do exactly as I say
      and no one gets hurt.

02:53.974 --> 02:55.774
                 You got it?

02:55.776 --> 02:58.710
                Get the cash
            out of the register.

02:58.712 --> 03:00.445
                     Now!
     [ Screams ]

03:00.447 --> 03:01.646
                      Go!
     [ Indistinct shouting ]

03:01.648 --> 03:03.715
                 Take this!
                Open the bag!

03:03.717 --> 03:04.983
          Get up, pregnant lady!

03:04.985 --> 03:08.052
  The rest of you, wallets out,
           right now!

03:08.054 --> 03:10.522
     See this?! Do as I say
     and no one'll get hurt!

03:10.524 --> 03:12.056
            Go, move!

03:12.058 --> 03:14.192
    Watches and jewelry, too!
        Fill up this bag!

03:14.194 --> 03:16.394
      Please don't hurt me!
         Please, please!
                  Hold it out!
               Hold out the bag!

03:16.396 --> 03:17.730
                  Go, move,
              move, move, move!

03:17.732 --> 03:19.264
          That's right. Shut up!

03:19.266 --> 03:20.799
       -Please! [ Shouts ]
    -Fill it up! Fill it up!

03:20.801 --> 03:23.736
       -You're hurting me!
           -Let's go!

03:23.738 --> 03:25.137
     Move.
          [ Cries out ]

03:25.139 --> 03:26.471
The cash in the bag.

03:26.473 --> 03:28.073
    Go! Hurry up!

03:28.075 --> 03:29.942
Let's go! Move, move!
          [ Cries out ]

03:29.944 --> 03:31.143
           [ Panting ]

03:31.145 --> 03:34.146
   If I hear cops,
  Mom and baby die!

03:34.148 --> 03:42.220
                     ♪♪

03:42.222 --> 03:43.288
                 [ Laughs ]

03:43.290 --> 03:44.523
              Whoo!

03:46.827 --> 03:49.161
       You did good, little man.
                  Did good.

03:49.163 --> 03:50.429
    It's a girl.

03:50.431 --> 03:53.498
         Feels like a boy to me.

03:53.500 --> 03:56.301
             Hey, Andrew, come
             on out and prove me
             right, you hear me?

03:56.303 --> 03:59.037
    Uh, "Andrew"?
                      Yeah.

03:59.039 --> 04:00.705
            After Andy Bathgate,

04:00.707 --> 04:02.441
          greatest hockey player
                of all time.

04:03.978 --> 04:05.177
                [ Laughing ]
             You don't like it?

04:05.179 --> 04:07.312
     [ Laughs ]

04:07.314 --> 04:09.381
               "Andy" for short.
 It doesn't matter.
   It's a girl.

04:09.383 --> 04:12.584
          [ Laughter ]

04:12.586 --> 04:15.854
              It's about $400.
               That's not bad.

04:15.856 --> 04:18.723
 So, there's a diner
     on the 101.

04:18.725 --> 04:20.725
 It's open 24 hours.

04:20.726 --> 04:23.728
Rich ranchers eating
their steak and eggs.

04:23.730 --> 04:26.731
          This was the last one.

04:26.733 --> 04:28.400
             Babe, you're slow.

04:28.402 --> 04:30.202
            And we're kinda hard
               to forget now.

04:30.204 --> 04:31.603
        We've been lucky so far.

04:31.605 --> 04:33.271
Well, this isn't enough.

04:33.273 --> 04:35.607
         Well, if we need money,
             I'll figure it out.

04:35.609 --> 04:37.009
      Oh, yeah?
                      Yeah.

04:37.011 --> 04:38.943
Well, what am I supposed to do
 while you do that?

04:38.945 --> 04:41.814
        Huh?

04:41.816 --> 04:43.816
       Worry about being a mama.

04:47.888 --> 04:53.358
    [ Footsteps approaching ]

04:53.360 --> 04:54.827
 She still in there?

04:56.430 --> 04:57.963
                    Yeah.

05:00.567 --> 05:03.168
Did you get any sleep?

05:03.170 --> 05:04.770
                     No.

05:07.441 --> 05:08.773
The house is trashed.

05:08.775 --> 05:10.843
     How come you didn't tell me
               you saw Angela

05:10.845 --> 05:13.112
      when I was looking for her
                 yesterday?

05:15.249 --> 05:16.915
      I forgot.

05:16.917 --> 05:19.084
I didn't think it was a big deal
    at the time.

05:20.921 --> 05:23.589
 Plus, she was fine
when I left her, so...

05:29.329 --> 05:31.530
        Look.

05:31.532 --> 05:34.266
      I-I know
that you care about her.

05:34.268 --> 05:36.401
      [ Sighs ]

05:36.403 --> 05:39.071
But this is what she does.

05:39.073 --> 05:42.675
Seen it 1,000 times.

05:42.677 --> 05:45.778
She gets sober and then she
falls right back in.

05:47.614 --> 05:49.581
  Just like my mom.

05:52.887 --> 05:54.819
This only ends one way.

05:54.821 --> 06:04.096
                     ♪♪

06:04.098 --> 06:13.305
                     ♪♪

06:13.307 --> 06:15.574
      [ Sighs ]

06:15.576 --> 06:17.509
      Wake up.

06:17.511 --> 06:19.644
                 [ Groans ]

06:19.646 --> 06:21.780
                    What?

06:21.782 --> 06:24.449
  Come on, get up.
                  [ Groans ]

06:24.451 --> 06:26.652
           [ Sighing ]

06:28.589 --> 06:29.854
   Come on, here.

06:29.856 --> 06:30.923
         Don't touch me.

06:30.925 --> 06:35.460
      [ Breathing heavily ]

06:35.462 --> 06:41.066
                     ♪♪

06:41.068 --> 06:43.535
                Who the hell
      do you think you are, huh?

06:43.537 --> 06:45.470
             Locking me in here
                 all night?

06:45.472 --> 06:46.805
I was doing you a favor.

06:46.807 --> 06:48.072
                    Well,
          you're a bag of dicks.

06:48.074 --> 06:49.341
Come on, we're gonna go
    for a drive.

06:49.343 --> 06:51.143
         No, I'm getting my shit
              and I'm leaving.

06:51.145 --> 06:52.811
          I'm not going anywhere
                  with you.
Get in my truck right now

06:52.813 --> 06:54.947
or I will tie you up
and throw you in the back.

07:00.487 --> 07:02.821
         [ Nick cooing ]
So, look, you have to, um,

07:02.823 --> 07:04.289
remember what the nurse said,
        okay?

07:04.291 --> 07:06.090
      [ Cellphone buzzes ]

07:06.092 --> 07:08.226
It's just like a burrito.
     [ Cellphone clicking ]

07:08.228 --> 07:10.696
      [ Cooing continues ]

07:13.099 --> 07:15.433
         Yo?

07:15.435 --> 07:18.036
 Are you listening?
      [ Cooing continues ]

07:18.038 --> 07:19.438
                    Yeah.

07:19.440 --> 07:22.507
               Like a burrito.

07:22.509 --> 07:24.309
      [ Cellphone buzzing ]

07:24.311 --> 07:26.578
 You're blowing up.

07:26.580 --> 07:28.380
                      Clients.
      [ Cellphone buzzes ]

07:28.382 --> 07:30.983
You just got out of the
hospital. They can't
wait five minutes?

07:30.985 --> 07:33.918
     Well, they're coke addicts,
                Craig, so no.

07:33.920 --> 07:36.188
      [ Cooing continues ]

07:36.190 --> 07:39.792
     Here we go.
                I'm impressed.

07:39.794 --> 07:41.526
[ Exhales deeply ]
    Oh, that's one cute burrito.

07:41.528 --> 07:43.061
     Mm-hmm.
         [ Nick cooing ]

07:43.063 --> 07:45.264
 [ Whispering ] Hey?
 You're ready to go?

07:47.934 --> 07:49.001
      [ Cooing continues ]

07:49.003 --> 07:51.470
 Hear from your mom?

07:51.472 --> 07:53.137
                     No.

07:53.139 --> 07:54.673
        Good.

07:54.675 --> 07:56.675
     You know she's just waiting
             for us to screw up

07:56.677 --> 07:59.011
      and then she'll call DCFS.

07:59.013 --> 08:01.279
  Yeah, that's not
    gonna happen.

08:01.281 --> 08:03.548
         [ Nick cooing ]

08:03.550 --> 08:06.118
      [ Seagulls calling ]

08:09.289 --> 08:11.623
                 [ Groans ]

08:11.625 --> 08:14.226
                 Well, uh...

08:14.228 --> 08:16.729
              Smurf still knows
           how to throw a party.

08:19.433 --> 08:21.834
Nice just to be able
to check out for a while.

08:21.836 --> 08:25.237
       [ Waves crashing ]

08:25.239 --> 08:27.106
 [ Inhales deeply ]

08:30.444 --> 08:32.177
You come to bed last night?

08:34.780 --> 08:36.315
     [ Stubs out cigarette ]

08:38.985 --> 08:41.720
        What's going on?

08:41.722 --> 08:43.688
            [ Sighs ]

08:47.327 --> 08:48.460
             Deran.

08:48.462 --> 08:51.263
[ Breathing heavily ]

08:51.265 --> 08:52.664
              Hey.

08:52.666 --> 08:57.335
[ Breathing heavily ]

08:57.337 --> 08:58.904
    Smurf knows.

09:02.609 --> 09:03.976
                 Knows what?

09:06.146 --> 09:08.213
   That you talked
    to the cops.

09:14.088 --> 09:16.088
           How did she find out?

09:16.090 --> 09:18.757
I don't know, but she wants me
    to handle it.

09:21.362 --> 09:23.828
                "Handle it"?

09:23.830 --> 09:25.364
            What does that mean?

09:27.568 --> 09:30.369
She wants me to kill you.

09:30.371 --> 09:32.104
       You told her I didn't say
              anything, right?

09:32.106 --> 09:34.239
   Doesn't matter.
           No, no, look, look,

09:34.241 --> 09:37.376
           I'm -- I'm gonna talk
                 to Smurf --
Adrian, it doesn't matter!
    It doesn't matter!

09:41.982 --> 09:44.849
      It doesn't matter...
              -No.

09:44.851 --> 09:46.985
        [ Both panting ]

09:46.987 --> 09:51.056
How do you think we've
been able to get away
with this for so long

09:51.058 --> 09:52.657
without ever getting caught?

09:52.659 --> 09:55.059
[ Breathing heavily ]

09:55.061 --> 09:57.529
 It's because Smurf
    handles shit

09:57.531 --> 10:01.800
    preemptively!
             [ Exhales sharply ]

10:01.802 --> 10:09.141
                     ♪♪

10:09.143 --> 10:11.743
[ Whispering ] If you stay here,
 you will be killed.

10:11.745 --> 10:19.418
                     ♪♪

10:19.420 --> 10:27.026
                     ♪♪

10:29.000 --> 10:35.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

10:36.970 --> 10:38.771
         We need coffee.

10:43.444 --> 10:45.911
                  Smurf up?

10:45.913 --> 10:47.446
         She's not here.
       [ Coffee pouring ]

10:47.448 --> 10:50.449
    She left with some people
    from La Jolla last night.

10:50.451 --> 10:52.317
     [ Coffee pot clatters ]

10:57.724 --> 11:00.926
    This place is a pig sty.

11:00.928 --> 11:01.993
                Clean it up.

11:01.995 --> 11:05.130
      [ Door slides open ]

11:05.132 --> 11:07.666
     [ Door slides closed ]

11:07.668 --> 11:12.671
                     ♪♪

11:12.673 --> 11:14.473
      [ Doorknob jostling ]

11:14.475 --> 11:17.742
      -What are you doing?
  -Hang on, I've almost got it.

11:17.744 --> 11:19.077
       Colin:
Let's just break a window.

11:19.079 --> 11:21.680
      [ The Grateful Dead's
    "Ramble on Rose" plays ]

11:21.682 --> 11:23.349
              See?

11:25.352 --> 11:29.020
  ♪ Just like Jack the Ripper ♪

11:29.022 --> 11:32.958
     ♪ Just like mojo hand ♪

11:32.960 --> 11:36.095
   ♪ Just like Billy Sunday ♪

11:36.097 --> 11:41.900
  ♪ In a shotgun ragtime band ♪

11:41.902 --> 11:43.568
How do you know they're
  not coming back?

11:43.570 --> 11:46.638
   ♪ Just like New York City ♪
              They're at work.

11:46.640 --> 11:50.375
      ♪ Just like Jericho ♪

11:50.377 --> 11:53.912
        ♪ Pace the halls
      and climb the walls ♪

11:53.914 --> 11:54.980
              [ Sighs heavily ]

11:54.982 --> 12:00.185
  ♪ And get out when they blow ♪

12:00.187 --> 12:01.252
              Mmm.

12:01.254 --> 12:05.124
  ♪ Did you say your name was ♪

12:05.126 --> 12:09.194
       ♪ Ramblin' Rose? ♪

12:09.196 --> 12:12.463
       ♪ Ramble on, baby ♪
So, what do you think?

12:12.465 --> 12:14.333
                         Uh...
      ♪ Settle down easy ♪

12:14.335 --> 12:15.867
               Is there a safe
                or something?

12:15.869 --> 12:19.404
We're not here for a job.

12:19.406 --> 12:21.273
  What do you think
    of the house?

12:23.811 --> 12:27.679
                  For what?

12:27.681 --> 12:29.748
 [ Inhales deeply ]

12:29.750 --> 12:32.083
For the three of us.

12:32.085 --> 12:33.752
           To live in.

12:33.754 --> 12:35.754
                  Someday.

12:35.756 --> 12:37.189
        What?

12:40.694 --> 12:42.427
       I wanted to surprise you.

12:42.429 --> 12:45.697
        Come on, isn't it great?
          [ Pats back ]

12:45.699 --> 12:48.700
   I mean, I would change a lot,
    like the floor, for example.

12:48.702 --> 12:51.837
  Ooh! I saw -- I saw this thing
               in a magazine.

12:51.839 --> 12:53.905
                 It's called
         a "sunken living room."

12:53.907 --> 12:56.041
         I thought that we could
           knock down that wall,

12:56.043 --> 12:57.376
     put it right through there.

12:57.378 --> 13:00.912
      Do the current owners
     know about your plans?

13:00.914 --> 13:03.048
         Mm.

13:03.050 --> 13:04.983
                  [ Scoffs ]
   [ Chuckles ]

13:04.985 --> 13:07.118
      How'd you find this place?

13:07.120 --> 13:09.320
Just driving around.

13:09.322 --> 13:10.055
                    Hmm.

13:10.057 --> 13:12.657
It was calling to me.

13:12.659 --> 13:15.727
  I like Oceanside.

13:15.729 --> 13:17.729
         Bakersfield by the bay.

13:17.731 --> 13:20.131
      [ Sighs ]

13:20.133 --> 13:23.134
  You really want to settle down
                 like this?

13:23.136 --> 13:26.405
     Like what?

13:26.407 --> 13:29.140
                Like we're...

13:29.142 --> 13:30.909
                   normal.

13:35.148 --> 13:37.249
Nothing's gonna change.

13:39.753 --> 13:41.620
  We're gonna do...

13:41.622 --> 13:44.289
     what we do.

13:44.291 --> 13:48.693
But <i> she's</i> gonna have
a yard to play in...

13:48.695 --> 13:51.029
            [ Sighs ]

13:51.031 --> 13:54.900
           ...bed to sleep in...

13:54.902 --> 13:56.969
             and enough to eat.

13:58.839 --> 14:01.973
            [ Sighs ]

14:01.975 --> 14:03.575
      Alright.

14:03.577 --> 14:10.916
                     ♪♪

14:10.918 --> 14:18.657
                     ♪♪

14:18.659 --> 14:26.197
                     ♪♪

14:26.199 --> 14:27.933
        [ Latch clicks ]

14:31.872 --> 14:33.538
         [ Gate closes ]

14:33.540 --> 14:38.877
                     ♪♪

14:38.879 --> 14:44.215
                     ♪♪

14:44.217 --> 14:45.684
[ Quietly ] Hey, man.

14:48.021 --> 14:51.156
     Meet Nick.

14:51.158 --> 14:53.492
    Wild, right?

14:53.494 --> 14:55.894
                    Yeah.

14:55.896 --> 14:58.229
  Oh, come on, man.
     He's cute.

14:58.231 --> 15:00.832
              Yeah, he's cute.

15:00.834 --> 15:03.168
Hey, Deran.

15:03.170 --> 15:05.170
   [ Quietly ] Hi.

15:05.172 --> 15:06.571
          [ Smooches ]

15:06.573 --> 15:08.373
            Congrats, he's huge.

15:08.375 --> 15:10.309
   Hey, you want to hold him?

15:13.380 --> 15:15.514
           No, man, maybe later.
                   I'm...

15:15.516 --> 15:17.048
                  Yeah, no.

15:17.050 --> 15:20.251
   You know what?
  It's time to eat.

15:20.253 --> 15:22.321
     [ Whispering ] Come on.

15:22.323 --> 15:23.522
 [ Whispering ] Hi.
          You got him?

15:23.524 --> 15:27.459
         [ Nick cooing ]
I've got him, got him.

15:27.461 --> 15:28.393
    You staying?

15:28.395 --> 15:30.129
                   Uh, no,
           I'm just stopping by.

15:30.131 --> 15:32.064
        Can -- Can I talk to you
                for a minute?

15:33.801 --> 15:36.001
         Yeah. Be back.

15:39.873 --> 15:42.808
       [ Seagulls crying ]

15:42.810 --> 15:48.814
       [ Waves crashing ]

15:48.816 --> 15:49.815
        Hey.

15:49.817 --> 15:52.251
That kid is your nephew.

15:54.155 --> 15:58.023
                I know, man.
             I'm sorry, alright?

15:58.025 --> 16:00.892
The hell's your problem?

16:00.894 --> 16:03.028
 You didn't know he was your kid
      until like three days ago.

16:03.030 --> 16:04.229
        I'm sorry if it takes me
                  a second.

16:04.231 --> 16:05.964
   That's my son.

16:05.966 --> 16:07.366
     My family.

16:07.368 --> 16:10.569
Which makes him <i> your</i> family.

16:10.571 --> 16:12.037
    You got that?

16:14.241 --> 16:15.741
               Yeah, I got it.

16:18.311 --> 16:19.712
   Alright, then.

16:23.917 --> 16:25.351
   So, what's up?

16:29.723 --> 16:31.923
          Look, I need passports
              for me and Adrian

16:31.925 --> 16:34.125
             under the aliases.

16:34.127 --> 16:35.394
        Why?

16:37.931 --> 16:41.066
 I need to get Adrian out of the
    country as soon as possible.

16:41.068 --> 16:42.534
             The DEA busted him.

16:42.536 --> 16:43.602
               They -- They --
         They caught him at LAX.

16:43.604 --> 16:45.404
              He was on his way
              to South Africa.

16:45.406 --> 16:48.073
          He -- He was smuggling
     a couple pounds of cocaine.

16:48.075 --> 16:50.742
    Uh, he was working for Jack.

16:50.744 --> 16:53.745
               His lawyer said
           he could do up to 15.

16:53.747 --> 16:55.346
    What, Adrian
was working for Jack?!

16:55.348 --> 16:56.681
             Look, I didn't know
                  about it

16:56.683 --> 16:58.016
               until after all
       that shit happened, okay?

16:58.018 --> 16:59.485
Wait, and that's why you want
  to hit that cop?

17:06.093 --> 17:08.093
  [ Sighs heavily ]

17:13.099 --> 17:15.401
Adrian knows a lot of shit.

17:17.438 --> 17:19.238
         What, Renn doesn't know
                 what we do?

17:19.240 --> 17:21.106
I haven't been telling her
  all the details.

17:21.108 --> 17:22.373
     Yeah, so what's your point?

17:22.375 --> 17:23.575
    My point is,

17:23.577 --> 17:25.175
 do we have anything
   to worry about?

17:25.178 --> 17:26.778
  <i> That's</i> my point.

17:26.780 --> 17:33.252
                     ♪♪

17:33.254 --> 17:40.125
                     ♪♪

17:40.127 --> 17:41.727
          Please do this for me.

17:44.932 --> 17:46.365
                   Please.

17:48.936 --> 17:50.201
        Okay.

17:50.203 --> 17:57.142
                     ♪♪

17:57.144 --> 17:58.744
           Mm-hmm. Mm.

18:02.683 --> 18:04.149
                    Here.

18:04.151 --> 18:06.485
               Hand that over.

18:06.487 --> 18:08.086
             Eat some real food.

18:08.088 --> 18:09.554
       This is <i> real</i> food?

18:09.556 --> 18:11.357
         It's better than candy.

18:15.428 --> 18:17.829
You got to take care
    of yourself.

18:17.831 --> 18:19.765
       Go on.

18:19.767 --> 18:20.899
        Hmm?

18:23.104 --> 18:24.235
        [ Sighs heavily ]

18:24.237 --> 18:27.372
        [ Knock on door ]

18:27.374 --> 18:29.508
        [ Gun clicking ]

18:38.185 --> 18:39.785
           Hey, Manny.

18:39.787 --> 18:41.286
       Janine.

18:48.862 --> 18:52.331
              I told him about
          the armored truck job.

18:52.333 --> 18:54.199
      And you're going with him.

19:01.208 --> 19:02.875
          [ Gun thuds ]

19:09.483 --> 19:11.216
     [ Quietly ]
   You called him?

19:11.218 --> 19:12.884
                 [ Quietly ]
       I knew that you wouldn't.
  Damn-straight.

19:12.886 --> 19:14.285
                          Hey.
Just gonna forget about
   what happened?

19:14.287 --> 19:16.355
                   Hey...
        Hmm?

19:16.357 --> 19:18.223
           He called me a whore.
     Mm-hmm.

19:18.225 --> 19:20.559
                And you tried
              to break his jaw.

19:20.561 --> 19:22.928
                   I'd say
            that we're all even.

19:26.767 --> 19:29.100
             We need the money.

19:29.102 --> 19:32.037
           And it's a solid job.

19:32.039 --> 19:33.705
       Checked out, Colin.

19:33.707 --> 19:35.841
       Should be a breeze,
          if you're in.

19:42.449 --> 19:44.249
      And what are you gonna do?

19:50.791 --> 19:52.524
     Stay home.

19:52.526 --> 19:54.325
  Wait for my cut.

19:54.327 --> 20:00.399
                     ♪♪

20:00.401 --> 20:06.605
                     ♪♪

20:06.607 --> 20:07.806
              Yeah.

20:11.012 --> 20:13.278
        Here?
                 Mm-hmm.

20:13.280 --> 20:14.679
     [ Indistinct chatter ]

20:14.681 --> 20:17.348
       -Nope! No, no, no!
     -[ Whispering ] Go in.

20:17.350 --> 20:20.351
   This isn't how
it works, Pope, okay?

20:20.353 --> 20:21.820
               [ Whispering ]
              You get in there.

20:23.957 --> 20:26.091
 [ Exhales sharply ]

20:26.093 --> 20:27.693
   [ Whispering ]
     Okay, fine.

20:27.695 --> 20:29.294
 Let's go, come on.

20:29.296 --> 20:39.405
     [ Indistinct chatter ]

20:43.577 --> 20:47.512
 Susie: It's good to see you all
   and thanks for being here.

20:47.514 --> 20:51.583
          Hardest part
      is showing up, right?

20:51.585 --> 20:53.985
          So, if we --
Cool if I talk first?

20:53.987 --> 20:57.188
         Uh, of course.

20:57.190 --> 20:59.724
      [ Sighs ]

20:59.726 --> 21:04.395
So, we all say secrets
   keep you sick.

21:04.397 --> 21:06.397
That's why we're here,
       right?

21:06.399 --> 21:09.400
    To be honest
so we can get better?

21:09.402 --> 21:11.136
That's what you want,
       right?

21:11.138 --> 21:12.403
      [ Huffs ]

21:12.405 --> 21:13.605
      Honesty?

21:17.078 --> 21:18.677
        Okay.

21:18.679 --> 21:21.280
  [ Sighs deeply ]

21:21.282 --> 21:24.015
      Showed up
at an old friend's house.

21:24.017 --> 21:27.352
 Her name was Julia.

21:27.354 --> 21:30.822
 But I wasn't really
  looking for her.

21:30.824 --> 21:33.292
   I already knew
    she was dead.

21:33.294 --> 21:36.962
     I found out
when I was in prison.

21:36.964 --> 21:39.898
I was really looking for her
mother and her money.

21:39.900 --> 21:42.101
   Julia's mother
  used to give her

21:42.103 --> 21:44.703
   stacks of cash
    to stay away.

21:44.705 --> 21:46.772
I was hoping she'd do
  the same for me.

21:49.510 --> 21:51.042
   Julia's brother
   was there, too.

21:51.044 --> 21:52.377
      He's 40,

21:52.379 --> 21:54.245
 and he still lives
at home with his mom.

21:54.247 --> 21:56.115
     [ Laughs ]

21:56.117 --> 21:59.318
How weird is that, right?

21:59.320 --> 22:01.520
    He liked me.

22:01.522 --> 22:02.787
So, I slept with him,

22:02.789 --> 22:04.923
  'cause I figured
  he'd let me stay.

22:07.995 --> 22:09.995
  It was all a con.

22:09.997 --> 22:11.262
 And he fell for it.

22:11.264 --> 22:17.602
                     ♪♪

22:17.604 --> 22:23.408
Thanks for letting me share.

22:23.410 --> 22:25.410
       Radio: <i> ...two days.</i>
     <i> Local officials report</i>

22:25.412 --> 22:27.078
      <i> that damage to homes</i>
          <i> in the area</i>

22:27.080 --> 22:28.947
  <i> will be at least $3 million.</i>

22:28.949 --> 22:31.683
        <i> Getting reports</i>
    <i> of a bold midday robbery</i>

22:31.685 --> 22:34.085
     <i> of an armored vehicle</i>
         <i> in San Marcos.</i>

22:34.087 --> 22:36.355
         <i> Police report</i>
   <i> masked assailants made off</i>

22:36.357 --> 22:38.423
    <i> with more than $25,000.</i>

22:38.425 --> 22:42.027
       [ Exhales sharply,
         stomping foot ]
  <i> More details as we get them.</i>

22:42.029 --> 22:43.762
       [ Inhales deeply ]

22:43.764 --> 22:45.564
          Oh, my God...

22:45.566 --> 22:47.166
            [ Sighs ]

22:47.168 --> 22:54.373
 ♪ All I need is some sunshine ♪

22:54.375 --> 22:56.375
         ♪ All I need ♪

22:56.377 --> 23:03.515
      [ Intercom ringing ]

23:03.517 --> 23:05.116
         [ Phone beeps ]

23:05.118 --> 23:06.785
        Smurf's not here.

23:06.787 --> 23:08.253
                  <i> I know.</i>

23:08.255 --> 23:10.756
       <i> I came to talk with you.</i>
      <i> It'll only take a minute.</i>

23:14.127 --> 23:15.594
      <i> It'll be worth your time.</i>

23:15.596 --> 23:19.330
       ♪ With another one
         for the caves ♪

23:19.332 --> 23:22.000
         [ Phone beeps ]

23:22.002 --> 23:28.807
        ♪ And in the tarn
     beyond those birches ♪

23:28.809 --> 23:33.011
  ♪ Is a spirit that I crave ♪

23:33.013 --> 23:40.485
 ♪ All I need is some sunshine ♪

23:40.487 --> 23:46.425
         ♪ All I need ♪

23:46.427 --> 23:48.827
          ♪ All I need ♪

23:48.829 --> 23:50.829
Looks like it was quite
     the party.

23:50.831 --> 23:53.232
      ♪ Is some sunshine ♪

23:53.234 --> 23:55.033
              What do you want?

23:55.035 --> 23:56.635
 [ Laughing ] Okay.

23:56.637 --> 23:58.604
 Right to the point.

24:00.574 --> 24:02.507
 I have another job.

24:02.509 --> 24:03.909
   I need a crew.

24:03.911 --> 24:07.112
                 [ Scoffs ]

24:07.114 --> 24:09.248
               First Craig...

24:09.250 --> 24:12.251
                then Smurf...

24:12.253 --> 24:15.054
                   now me.

24:15.056 --> 24:16.588
      If you need a crew so bad,

24:16.590 --> 24:18.557
   why don't you put in the work
              and get your own?

24:20.728 --> 24:24.395
We're not so different,
     you and me.

24:24.397 --> 24:25.898
     Survivors.

24:27.868 --> 24:29.868
Which is a good thing
because this whole thing's

24:29.870 --> 24:33.004
  gonna fall apart
 when Smurf's gone.

24:33.006 --> 24:34.740
Unless you take over.

24:34.742 --> 24:36.742
     Smurf's not going anywhere.

24:36.744 --> 24:40.612
       Really?
I heard she has cancer.

24:40.614 --> 24:42.013
I assume it's fatal,

24:42.015 --> 24:44.783
otherwise you wouldn't have
risked going to see Gia.

24:46.620 --> 24:48.087
It's a small world, J.

24:48.089 --> 24:51.756
People notice when you make
  a move like that.

24:51.758 --> 24:53.759
    So, why don't
  you start acting

24:53.761 --> 24:57.363
like the leader you're <i> clearly</i>
   wanting to be?

25:00.901 --> 25:02.735
               What's the job?

25:06.307 --> 25:08.373
          Yes, yeah, yeah, yeah!

25:08.375 --> 25:11.910
        Whoo!
Yeah!
    Details. Details, please?

25:11.912 --> 25:13.512
        There wasn't much
          on the news.

25:13.514 --> 25:15.380
     Jake: What's there to tell?
               It went great.

25:15.382 --> 25:16.782
                Had that shit
             locked down tight.

25:16.784 --> 25:19.250
              Whoo!
         Smooth as silk!

25:19.252 --> 25:21.920
      [ Breathing heavily ]
   Hey, hey, souvenir for you.

25:21.922 --> 25:25.256
                            Oh!
        From that guard's
         ankle holster.

25:25.258 --> 25:27.058
             -Yeah.
             -Here.

25:27.060 --> 25:28.927
                [ Whistles ]

25:28.929 --> 25:30.595
            $26,500.

25:30.597 --> 25:33.132
          -Hell, yeah.
     -[ Slams table ] Whoo!

25:33.134 --> 25:35.867
  It's pretty nice.

25:35.869 --> 25:38.003
   It's 3 grand more than our
         biggest score.

25:40.273 --> 25:42.941
      You did great, babe.
 Shit.

25:42.943 --> 25:44.275
           Come here.

25:44.277 --> 25:46.478
         You did great.

25:46.480 --> 25:49.414
         Alright, uh...

25:49.416 --> 25:52.151
   May we all get what we want

25:52.153 --> 25:55.754
   but never what we deserve.
           -[ Laughs ]

25:55.756 --> 25:59.090
      Ain't that the truth?

25:59.092 --> 26:01.426
     Pope: Hey.

26:01.428 --> 26:02.828
Hey, where you going?!

26:02.830 --> 26:06.097
      Look, I'm not Julia, okay?

26:06.099 --> 26:07.032
        What?

26:07.034 --> 26:08.167
                You heard me.

26:08.169 --> 26:09.568
This isn't about <i> Julia.</i>

26:09.570 --> 26:11.370
                    Yeah,
       dragging me to a meeting.

26:11.372 --> 26:13.972
        Of course, it is.
           -Whatever.

26:13.974 --> 26:18.043
When was the last time
you saw her, Pope, huh?

26:18.045 --> 26:20.712
  When J was three?

26:20.714 --> 26:22.781
They lived <i> a mile away</i>

26:22.783 --> 26:24.916
     and you abandoned her,

26:24.918 --> 26:26.185
all -- all 'cause you
  believed the shit

26:26.187 --> 26:28.787
     that Smurf
was always saying about her?

26:28.789 --> 26:31.122
  Or was it because
   she loved Baz?

26:31.124 --> 26:33.058
   [ Stammering ]
  Make you jealous

26:33.060 --> 26:36.061
that she loved someone in
Smurf's house of horrors

26:36.063 --> 26:38.263
   other than you,
     is that it?
                     Shut up.

26:38.265 --> 26:41.600
She was your twin sister
 and she needed you!

26:41.602 --> 26:44.069
<i> God,</i> she needed you
 and she loved you.

26:44.071 --> 26:45.871
  She never stopped
     loving you.

26:45.873 --> 26:47.939
She was always waiting
for you to knock on her door

26:47.941 --> 26:49.074
 and you never did!

26:49.076 --> 26:52.411
  You chose Mommy,
 and then she died.

26:52.413 --> 26:55.547
   That is on you.

26:55.549 --> 26:57.716
  And there are no
   do-overs, Pope.

27:02.289 --> 27:04.155
            [ Gruffly ] Why not?

27:04.157 --> 27:12.898
                     ♪♪

27:12.900 --> 27:16.034
   [ Car door opens, closes ]

27:16.036 --> 27:25.644
                     ♪♪

27:25.646 --> 27:35.654
                     ♪♪

27:35.656 --> 27:36.788
         [ Door closes ]

27:36.790 --> 27:41.526
                     ♪♪

27:41.528 --> 27:43.495
            [ Swallows heavily ]

27:44.465 --> 27:46.465
    Look, just...
   drive me home.

27:46.467 --> 27:48.267
  I'll get my shit
    and go, okay?

27:48.269 --> 27:50.769
      [ Sighs ]

27:53.540 --> 27:55.006
You hate me now, right?

27:55.008 --> 28:01.080
                     ♪♪

28:01.082 --> 28:02.481
                     No.

28:02.483 --> 28:07.218
                     ♪♪

28:07.220 --> 28:09.821
               Nobody tells me
                 the truth.

28:09.823 --> 28:16.628
                     ♪♪

28:16.630 --> 28:19.698
      Wasn't...
 [ Exhales sharply ]

28:19.700 --> 28:25.170
    It wasn't all
about the money, okay?

28:25.172 --> 28:26.739
   You know that.

28:28.842 --> 28:31.643
      You're done with that shit

28:31.645 --> 28:33.712
              if you're staying
                at the house.

28:36.317 --> 28:37.316
      I'll try.

28:37.318 --> 28:38.583
         That's not good enough.

28:38.585 --> 28:40.585
Well, it's the truth.

28:40.587 --> 28:42.453
 [ Exhales sharply ]

28:42.455 --> 28:43.588
        What?

28:43.590 --> 28:45.791
You think I wanted this
     to happen?

28:45.793 --> 28:47.192
     [ Laughs ]

28:47.194 --> 28:50.195
I was clean three years
and now I'm back to nothing.

28:50.197 --> 28:52.664
        I thought you were doing
                  so good.

28:52.666 --> 28:54.866
[ Breathing heavily ]

28:54.868 --> 28:56.735
    I was. I <i> was.</i>

28:56.737 --> 28:59.538
      [ Sighs ]

28:59.540 --> 29:02.674
I don't know what happened.
        I...

29:02.676 --> 29:04.075
 [ Exhales heavily ]

29:04.077 --> 29:06.545
J took me to Kalani's
  for lunch and...

29:06.547 --> 29:08.947
      [ Sighs ]

29:08.949 --> 29:12.884
          J took you to Kalani's
                 for lunch?

29:12.886 --> 29:17.022
              [ Sighs slowly ]

29:17.024 --> 29:19.624
  Look, I'm the one
 who did this, okay?

29:19.626 --> 29:22.694
         Me.

29:22.696 --> 29:24.963
   I just slipped.

29:24.965 --> 29:26.899
I can't blame J for that.

29:28.635 --> 29:31.603
        [ Engine starts ]

29:36.711 --> 29:39.711
 [ The Dogs' "I'm Alive" plays ]

29:39.713 --> 29:44.249
                     ♪♪

29:44.251 --> 29:46.985
       ♪ I'm alive, baby ♪

29:46.987 --> 29:48.854
      [ Engine shuts off ]

29:51.191 --> 29:52.658
       [ Car door closes ]

29:56.063 --> 29:57.830
      [ Car doors closing ]

30:08.742 --> 30:11.743
         [ Rick Coyne's
    "Had You So Long" plays ]

30:11.745 --> 30:14.947
              Hey.

30:14.949 --> 30:17.416
Yeah, let's get some beer.

30:17.418 --> 30:25.223
                     ♪♪

30:25.225 --> 30:27.660
                  Mnh-mnh.
                  Mnh-mnh.

30:29.296 --> 30:31.563
       [ Plastic rustles ]

30:31.565 --> 30:33.698
         [ Both laugh ]

30:33.700 --> 30:34.967
All she wants is sugar.

30:34.969 --> 30:37.702
                 It's a boy.

30:37.704 --> 30:39.872
          -It's a girl.
            -Mnh-mnh.

30:43.978 --> 30:47.446
      [ Brakes squealing ]

30:47.448 --> 30:49.848
      [ Engine shuts off ]

30:55.255 --> 30:57.522
She also wants a Coke.

30:57.524 --> 30:59.992
                  Oh, yeah?

30:59.994 --> 31:01.193
            Want me to get that?

31:01.195 --> 31:02.394
            -Mm-hmm.
            -Alright.

31:02.396 --> 31:04.128
         [ Both laugh ]

31:04.130 --> 31:10.402
                     ♪♪

31:10.404 --> 31:12.136
 Getting close, huh?

31:12.138 --> 31:13.806
  Looks like you're
 about ready to pop.

31:15.476 --> 31:18.010
[ Muttering ] I hope that's not
    what happens.

31:18.012 --> 31:21.079
                    Huh.

31:21.081 --> 31:22.947
                Pack of Reds.

31:22.949 --> 31:30.288
                     ♪♪

31:30.290 --> 31:37.962
                     ♪♪

31:37.964 --> 31:39.698
            You have a nice day.

31:39.700 --> 31:41.366
 You, too, Officer.

31:41.368 --> 31:47.972
                     ♪♪

31:47.974 --> 31:49.374
         [ Door closes ]

31:49.376 --> 31:52.945
                     ♪♪

31:57.051 --> 32:00.118
                     ♪♪

32:00.120 --> 32:03.321
    [ Police radio chatter ]

32:03.323 --> 32:04.656
        Where's that APB
       on those robberies

32:04.658 --> 32:07.125
   with the pregnant hostage?

32:07.127 --> 32:08.993
            The diner stick-ups?

32:08.995 --> 32:09.794
        Why?

32:09.796 --> 32:13.265
             Just let me see it.

32:13.267 --> 32:16.268
    [ Footsteps approaching ]

32:16.270 --> 32:21.273
                     ♪♪

32:21.275 --> 32:29.147
         [ Door closes ]

32:29.149 --> 32:30.949
                 Hey? Miss?

32:30.951 --> 32:33.085
         [ Door closes ]
    [ Footsteps approaching ]

32:33.087 --> 32:35.487
      Hey, hey, whoa. Hey.

32:35.489 --> 32:37.422
      Uh, we --
we don't want any trouble.

32:37.424 --> 32:40.492
         Hey, take it easy, man.
             Just take it easy.

32:40.494 --> 32:47.099
                     ♪♪

32:47.101 --> 32:48.567
     Back, back!

32:48.569 --> 32:49.835
       Inside.

32:51.705 --> 32:53.906
      [ Gunshots continue ]
    Hey! Get down! Watch out!

32:53.908 --> 32:54.907
      Back up!

32:54.909 --> 32:56.508
      [ Gunshots continue ]

32:56.510 --> 32:57.910
Shots fired, shots fired!

32:57.912 --> 32:59.244
    Officer down!
    Send back-up!

32:59.246 --> 33:00.378
        Colin: Stay down.

33:00.380 --> 33:01.580
           [ Gunfire ]

33:01.582 --> 33:11.590
                     ♪♪

33:11.592 --> 33:12.925
        [ Gunshot fires ]
                 [ Grunts ]

33:12.927 --> 33:15.794
      [ Gunfire continues ]

33:18.198 --> 33:21.466
           [ Grunts ]

33:21.468 --> 33:24.136
   [ Shouts ] Go!

33:24.138 --> 33:27.672
               Go!

33:27.674 --> 33:28.607
       Drive!

33:28.609 --> 33:33.478
                     ♪♪

33:33.480 --> 33:37.616
       [ Tires squealing ]

33:37.618 --> 33:43.655
                     ♪♪

33:49.830 --> 33:51.429
                    Jake:
         What the hell happened?

33:51.431 --> 33:53.498
            Everything was cool!
                Jesus Christ!

33:53.500 --> 33:54.767
        He had to do it.

33:54.769 --> 33:56.835
         -Shoot a cop?!
   -He had a gun in his hand!

33:56.837 --> 33:59.037
   Look, both of you, shut up!

33:59.039 --> 34:00.973
     Look, let's -- let's --
      let's go to Temecula.

34:00.975 --> 34:03.041
      I got a chick there.
       We can use her car.

34:03.043 --> 34:05.377
     Let's get out of town.
         Take Route 157!

34:05.379 --> 34:07.512
       [ Engine slowing ]

34:07.514 --> 34:09.447
  Colin, why you slowing down?

34:09.449 --> 34:10.514
               What the hell?

34:10.516 --> 34:11.850
   Janine: Colin?

34:11.851 --> 34:13.652
              Manny: Colin? Hey!
        [ Horn honking ]

34:13.654 --> 34:15.520
       Colin?

34:15.522 --> 34:17.922
   Colin, we're...

34:17.924 --> 34:18.857
       Colin?!
                    Oh, shit.

34:18.859 --> 34:21.994
 Oh, my God! Colin!
       Colin!

34:21.996 --> 34:23.862
 We have to get him
